        <updateDate>2021-06-23T18:56:12Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><strong>Clean Slate Act of 2021</strong></p> <p>This bill establishes a framework for sealing records related to certain federal criminal offenses.</p> <p>Courts must automatically seal records related to (1) a conviction for simple possession of a controlled substance or for any nonviolent offense involving marijuana, or (2) an arrest for an offense that does not result in a conviction. </p> <p>Additionally, an individual who meets certain criteria may petition to seal records related to a conviction for other nonviolent offenses. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
